        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Di</supplied>s <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>m<expan><ex>o</ex><abbr>n</abbr><ex>umen</ex><abbr>t</abbr></expan><expan><ex>u</ex><abbr>m</abbr></expan> <lb n="3"/>Pauliani <lb n="4"/>Pauli filius <note>sic</note> <lb n="5"/>Annicens<lb break="no" n="6"/>a <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex cert="low">oniugi</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex cert="low">at</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Spitz zulaufender Grabpfeiler/Pyramidion (&amp;apos;obélisque lingon&amp;apos;), oben und rechts unten abgebrochen. Maßangaben nach Le Gouz de Gerland: Höhe: 4 pieds 4 p(ouces) (~141 cm); Breite 2 pieds 2 p(ouces) 7 l(ignes): (~72 cm). E mit zwei senkrechten Hasten wiedergegeben (sog. &amp;apos;gallisches&amp;apos; E). (B): Le Bohec; Provost - Périchon : Z. 6: /a C D; Lejay: Z. 1: [D(is) M(anibus)] / s(acrum) M(o)[n(u)]/m(e)nt(u)m; Z. 5/6: Annicen(u)s / a c d??; Joubeaux: Z. 1: &amp;lt;D&amp;gt;(is) M(anibus); Z. 5/6: Annicens. (?) / A C D. (?).</p>
            </div>
